					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This is fragmentary. It seems to record a gift of 144 sheep for burning perpetual lamps in the temple with <hi rend="italic">anuḻakku</hi> and half of ghee suplied daily by the recipient. This must be a later inscription, since mention is made of <hi rend="italic">Jayaṉkoṇḍa</hi> which was a title of <hi rend="bold">Rājarāja I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
